It's time to tear down our bedroom. The last room in the house that hasn't been touched except for a little decorating.
The awful electric fireplace and the fireplace hearth need to come out. We have to brick up the fireplace, replace the chipped plaster, and smooth it. Then build a custom-made wardrobe.
We always start with a rough pencil sketch...
The dirty part of the work is done.
At the back of the chimney, we found a few dead birds, very dried up :(
Everything is ready for the stucco artist next week.
The small side niche has become good.
Here comes a new wardrobe (but we haven't even started on the design yet 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the heater!
And we even thought about including this nice little vent flap, so that the chimney doesn't get damp.
The chimney sweep has installed the cover and hood. Now it should be a bit safer for the ravens that like to nest there. 🪺
The plasterer is done. Tomorrow, the floor will be laid!
The cork mat is lying, I've built a toilet paper roll sawdust extractor for the vacuum cleaner 😂
Floor tiles are ready and can be laid. We are currently having tea break.
Buhu. Progress is slow today because of these super complicated cuts around the door posts, so that we can have a smooth transition to the hallway (where the floor will also be replaced). @user45@twitter.com has cursed me.
Done, but at the end! The climax was the terrible assembly instructions for the new bed. We'll sleep well tonight!
The floor in the hallway and all the baseboards are still missing. The decorator comes in a month, so we currently have a rough plaster look.
A little more DIY work in the evening, to cut or chisel out the lower sections around the doorposts, so that the floor can fit seamlessly underneath.
The cork mat is now also in the hallway.
Yesterday, we finished the floor in the hallway! Then we left at 5 a.m. to pick up item 1 at Heathrow, then a quick nap and a final sprint in the hallway, the planks are installed. The joints will be done once the adhesive is dry.
